Description: Body sherd of Corinthian pottery open vessel, probably a black-figured column-krater; interior glazed black; exterior: traces of two worn black bands on lower part of sherd; inscription on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 335)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 671, no. 296)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.196) (phase 3)
